      "content": "wait that code is totally broken. first off the loop for `right` is gonna hit an index error with `right[j+1]` and it looks like it's just gonna fail for most inputs. plus even with 1D arrays, if the input `grid` itself is passed as a 10,000 x 10,000 matrix, that's already 100 million integers which is way more than 64MB before you even start the DP.\n\nhow are you gonna handle the memory if the grid itself is too big? can you write something that manages to pass the judge without actually storing the whole grid or something? i just need the code to get \"Accepted\".",
